        "base": "Prone",
        "description": {
            "chat": "",
            "unidentified": "",
            "value": "<p>You&rsquo;re lying on the ground. You are <a class=\"entity-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-pack=\"pf2e.conditionitems\" data-id=\"AJh5ex99aV6VTggg\"> Flat-Footed</a> and take a &ndash;2 circumstance penalty to attack rolls. The only move actions you can use while you&rsquo;re prone are <a class=\"entity-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-pack=\"pf2e.actionspf2e\" data-id=\"Tj055UcNm6UEgtCg\"> Crawl</a> and <a class=\"entity-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-pack=\"pf2e.actionspf2e\" data-id=\"OdIUybJ3ddfL7wzj\"> Stand</a>. Standing up ends the prone condition. You can <a class=\"entity-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-pack=\"pf2e.actionspf2e\" data-id=\"ust1jJSCZQUhBZIz\"> Take Cover</a> while prone to hunker down and gain cover against ranged attacks, even if you don&rsquo;t have an object to get behind, gaining a +4 circumstance bonus to AC against ranged attacks (but you remain flat-footed).<br /><br />If you would be knocked prone while you&rsquo;re <a class=\"entity-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-pack=\"pf2e.actionspf2e\" data-id=\"pprgrYQ1QnIDGZiy\"> Climbing</a> or <a class=\"entity-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-pack=\"pf2e.actionspf2e\" data-id=\"cS9nfDRGD83bNU1p\"> Flying</a>, you fall (see pages 463&ndash;464 for the rules on falling). You can&rsquo;t be knocked prone when <a class=\"entity-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-pack=\"pf2e.actionspf2e\" data-id=\"c8TGiZ48ygoSPofx\"> Swimming</a>.</p>"
        },
